# VoxCPM2 endpoint. LOCAL-FIRST: defaults to the managed local server
# (scripts/voxcpm-local.sh -> http://localhost:7860), which gives full control over
# inference_timesteps/retry_badcase (the biggest stability/quality levers, locked out on the
# public Space). Point this at the public/demo Space to use remote inference instead.
# HF_VOXCPM2_URL=http://localhost:7860
HF_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=60000
HF_INFERENCE_TIMEOUT=300000
# Optional: extra /generate args for a NON-local self-hosted Space whose signature exposes more
# controls than the public demo, e.g.:  VOXCPM2_EXTRA_PARAMS=[20, true]
# (Ignored when local — the local server gets [inference_timesteps, retry_badcase] automatically.)
# VOXCPM2_EXTRA_PARAMS=
# QA only: keep an un-mastered "_raw" sibling of each new generation so History shows a
# raw-vs-mastered A/B player on identical content. Unset/0 in normal use.
# THALIKA_KEEP_RAW_OUTPUT=1
# "Start local" button runs this to launch the local VoxCPM2 server (local-server/server.py)
# on :7860. Defaults to the repo launcher; override only if you run VoxCPM differently.
# Local dev/desktop only. See local-server/README.md for Python requirements (3.10-3.12).
# VOXCPM_LOCAL_CMD=bash scripts/voxcpm-local.sh
GEMINI_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=60000
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_google_gemini_api_key_here
